snippet.textDisplay:
I love when the best YouTubers push out a 30+ minute video so when I saw this at 45 I was stooooked! Amazing content and very impressive to have a successful run in a rig you put together on the second attempt.

One thing I did notice was that the metal spatula seemed to have a concave bottom which trapped some liquid underneath the aerogel. I'm wondering if that contributed to a pressure differential in the final drying step and possibly the cracking of the first run.

I also didn't notice a curve on the spatula at first... So I'm also wondering if it was just the increased pressure that caused that.
